posts.body:
Just made this ID with ZeroID. I'm running Tor only and the Tor Browser. Worked fine. Exit node was: 195.176.3.24

Either a) That exit node hadn't sent enough requests to trigger ZID's throttling. b) ZID isn't using a blacklist that is exhaustive. Or, third possibility, you are a bunch of dumb faggits that got me worked up for nothing.

Also ZeroUP doesn't actually seem to work through Tor Browser. Haven't checked it with a regular browser....

>>2faba07c-5c3d-4868-8773-386842ec4947
Maybe click "New Identity" in Tor Browser to get a new exit node. My best guess at this point is that it has something to do with that.

>>a58bc65b-9c46-4d1c-844f-01502e193f7d
Weird. The only thing I did different was make a new fresh install of ZN and TB. So I was starting from scratch.

I noticed that ZID has an option for Bitmessage based registration. Might be another possible path

14. Livestreaming capabilities

Who needs justification? Livestreaming? Heck yeah!

>>65b469f3-79c3-407f-a4f4-1c6103dcd4bf
Ah, good catch. I think it is likely you are correct.

I feel better that the bad actor is likely some weird wrecker than ZID's developer.

>>3abe5f46-1cf0-466c-8364-4b8e5e1c61d5
I'm certainly not an expert in ZN internals but isn't all the code that is run on the client side in the data directory for each Zite?

Aside from wanting to know what code is run on the server backend for future reference, do we even care from a security standpoint? I'd be more worried about bugs in ZN's core code.
